               <p>JONAH SMITH WELLS. I live in Zion-gardens, Aldermanbury. On the 30th of June, about eight o'clock in the evening, I was on <placeName id="t18310630-102-crimeloc549">Ludgate-hill</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18310630-102-crimeloc549" type="placeName" value="Ludgate-hill"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310630-102-crimeloc549" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310630-102-off547 t18310630-102-crimeloc549"></join>, coming home, and felt something at my coat pocket - I turned round, saw my handkerchief in the prisoner's hands, and collared him; he was alone - I saw a Policeman, and gave him in charge - he endeavoured to secrete my handkerchief.</p>
               <p>FRANCIS WARDEN. I was in company with Mr. Wells. I saw him collar the prisoner, and take the handkerchief from him.</p>
               <p>WILLIAM BECK. I received him in charge.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>

               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I picked up the gentleman's handkerchief - he turned round, said it was his, and took it out of my hand.</p>
               <p>MR. WELLS. It was in his hand when I seized him and he put it into his breast - he did not say he had picked it up, but complained of my tearing his clothes.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18310630-102-verdict550" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18310630-102-verdict550" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 18. - <rs id="t18310630-102-punish551" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18310630-102-punish551" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310630-102-defend806 t18310630-102-punish551"></join>
               Transported for Life
            </rs>.</p>
